Yes. I'm sorry.

549
00:43:24,251 --> 00:43:26,251
This girl has a guardian
who keeps her locked away,

550
00:43:26,286 --> 00:43:28,604
but then, this morning,
she dropped this.

551
00:43:28,671 --> 00:43:30,755
Surely a sign that Johanna
wants me to help her.

552
00:43:30,823 --> 00:43:32,424
That's her name, Johanna.

553
00:43:32,492 --> 00:43:34,042
And Turpin is her guardian.

554
00:43:34,110 --> 00:43:35,761
He's a judge of some sort.

555
00:43:35,829 --> 00:43:37,780
Once he goes to court, I'm
going to slip into the house,

556
00:43:37,847 --> 00:43:40,298
release her and beg her to
come away with me tonight.

557
00:43:40,366 --> 00:43:41,934
Oh, this is very romantic.

558
00:43:42,001 --> 00:43:43,685
Yes.

559
00:43:43,753 --> 00:43:45,854
But I don't know anyone
in London, you see.

560
00:43:45,922 --> 00:43:49,958
And I need somewhere safe to bring her
till I've hired a coach to take us away.

561
00:43:50,026 --> 00:43:52,110
If I could keep her here
just for an hour or two,

562
00:43:52,129 --> 00:43:54,547
I'd be forever in your debt.

563
00:43:58,101 --> 00:43:59,735
Bring her here, love.

564
00:44:00,269 --> 00:44:02,020
Thank you, ma'am.

565
00:44:02,589 --> 00:44:03,989
Mr. Todd?

566
00:44:05,842 --> 00:44:06,875
Oh, thank you.

567
00:44:07,027 --> 00:44:09,879
Thank you, thank you, my friend.
Thank you, ma'am.

568
00:44:12,949 --> 00:44:16,502
Seems like the Fates are
favoring you at last, Mr. T.

569
00:44:17,904 --> 00:44:21,440
What is it? You'll have her
back before the day is out.

570
00:44:22,174 --> 00:44:23,508
What about him?

571
00:44:24,444 --> 00:44:25,644
Him?

572
00:44:25,712 --> 00:44:28,347
Oh, well. Let him bring her here.

573
00:44:28,414 --> 00:44:31,350
And then, since you're
so hot for a little,

574
00:44:32,452 --> 00:44:35,137
that's the throat to slit, my dear.

575
00:44:36,840 --> 00:44:38,640
Poor little Johanna.

576
00:44:38,708 --> 00:44:42,594
All those years without a
scrap of motherly affection.

577
00:44:42,661 --> 00:44:45,797
Well, I'll soon see to that.

578
00:44:53,974 --> 00:44:57,359
Hello. What's he doing here?

579
00:44:59,346 --> 00:45:01,563
Keep the boy downstairs.

580
00:45:12,842 --> 00:45:15,311
Signora, is Mr. Todd at home?

581
00:45:15,378 --> 00:45:17,346
Plying his trade upstairs.

582
00:45:17,414 --> 00:45:18,514
Oh...

583
00:45:18,582 --> 00:45:20,282
Would you look at it now?

584
00:45:20,350 --> 00:45:22,918
You wouldn't mind if I gave it a
nice juicy meat pie, would you?

585
00:45:22,969 --> 00:45:24,803
Si, si, si.
Whatever you want.

586
00:45:25,505 --> 00:45:27,172
Come on, lad.

587
00:45:27,239 --> 00:45:29,675
Your teeth are strong, I hope.

588
00:45:31,177 --> 00:45:32,978
Close the door.

589
00:45:33,045 --> 00:45:34,780
Get you a nice lovely pie.

590
00:45:37,584 --> 00:45:39,952
Sit down. Make yourself comfy.

591
00:45:47,477 --> 00:45:48,844
Come in.

592
00:45:57,703 --> 00:45:59,154
Mr. Todd.

593
00:45:59,222 --> 00:46:00,672
Signor Pirelli.

594
00:46:02,008 --> 00:46:04,476
Call me Davey.

595
00:46:04,543 --> 00:46:09,081
Davey Collin's the name
when it's not professional.

596
00:46:09,148 --> 00:46:11,783
I'd like me five quid back,
if you don't mind.

597
00:46:11,785 --> 00:46:12,818
Why?

598
00:46:12,886 --> 00:46:14,570
Because you entered
into our little wager

599
00:46:14,638 --> 00:46:16,855
under false pretenses, my friend.

600
00:46:16,923 --> 00:46:21,693
So that you might remember to be a
bit more forthright in the future,

601
00:46:21,761 --> 00:46:23,729
I'll be taking half your
profits from herewith.

602
00:46:23,796 --> 00:46:25,831
Share and share alike.

603
00:46:27,200 --> 00:46:29,818
Mr. Benjamin Barker.

604
00:46:32,204 --> 00:46:35,207
Here we are. Tuck in.

605
00:46:38,861 --> 00:46:41,964
I like to see a man with
a healthy appetite.

606
00:46:42,032 --> 00:46:44,732
Reminds me of my dear Albert.

607
00:46:44,800 --> 00:46:48,353
Liked to gorge himself
to bloatation, he did.

608
00:46:48,421 --> 00:46:50,839
He didn't have your nice
head of hair, though.

609
00:46:50,907 --> 00:46:54,176
To tell the truth,
it gets awful hot.

610
00:46:58,247 --> 00:47:00,599
Yes, this'll do nicely.

611
00:47:04,137 --> 00:47:05,804
You don't remember me, do you?

612
00:47:05,872 --> 00:47:07,456
Why should you?

613
00:47:07,523 --> 00:47:09,925
I was just a little nip that you
hired for a couple of weeks,

614
00:47:09,993 --> 00:47:11,994
sweeping up hair.

615
00:47:12,895 --> 00:47:15,730
But I remember these.

616
00:47:15,798 --> 00:47:18,884
And how could I ever
forget you, Mr. Barker.

617
00:47:23,139 --> 00:47:26,208
I used to sit right here.

618
00:47:26,276 --> 00:47:29,311
Dream of the day when I could
be a proper barber myself.

619
00:47:29,379 --> 00:47:33,114
You might say that you
was inspiration to me.

620
00:47:45,311 --> 00:47:47,212
So, is we got a deal?

621
00:47:48,564 --> 00:47:50,598
Or should I run down the street

622
00:47:50,666 --> 00:47:52,634
to me old pal, Beadle Bamford?

623
00:47:56,239 --> 00:47:57,889
What do you say to that, now,

624
00:47:57,957 --> 00:48:00,426
Mr. Sweeney Todd?

625
00:48:23,082 --> 00:48:26,134
My, my, my. Always work to be done.

626
00:48:26,202 --> 00:48:28,603
Spic and span, that's my motto.

627
00:48:41,233 --> 00:48:44,836
So, how'd you end up with
that dreadful Italian?

628
00:48:44,904 --> 00:48:46,288
Got me from the workhouse.

629
00:48:46,356 --> 00:48:48,540
Been there since I was born.

630
00:48:49,175 --> 00:48:50,392
Oh, God!

631
00:48:50,460 --> 00:48:53,512
He's got an appointment with his tailor!
If he's late, he'll blame me!

632
00:48:53,579 --> 00:48:54,879
Wait!

633
00:49:01,404 --> 00:49:04,072
Signor! You got an appointment!

634
00:49:09,445 --> 00:49:11,146
Signor Pirelli's been called away.

635
00:49:11,214 --> 00:49:13,965
Better run after him.

636
00:49:14,033 --> 00:49:18,420
No, sir. I should stay here,
or it'll be a lashing.

637
00:49:18,488 --> 00:49:21,339
He's a great one for the lashings.

638
00:49:27,130 --> 00:49:28,430
So,

639
00:49:29,598 --> 00:49:31,483
Mrs. Lovett gave
you a pie, did she?

640
00:49:31,550 --> 00:49:33,785
She's a real lady.

641
00:49:34,337 --> 00:49:36,087
That she is.

642
00:49:40,910 --> 00:49:43,562
But if I know a growing boy,

643
00:49:43,629 --> 00:49:45,963
there's still room
for more pie, eh?

644
00:49:46,031 --> 00:49:48,534
Yes, sir.

645
00:49:48,601 --> 00:49:51,420
Then why don't you wait for
your master downstairs?

646
00:49:51,487 --> 00:49:53,689
Be another pie in it
for you, I'm sure.

647
00:49:53,756 --> 00:49:55,891
No, I should stay here.

648
00:49:58,611 --> 00:50:02,513
Tell you what, why don't
you tell Mrs. Lovett

649
00:50:02,581 --> 00:50:06,051
that I said to give you
a nice big tot of gin.

650
00:50:06,119 --> 00:50:07,736
Thank you, sir!

651
00:51:15,788 --> 00:51:18,156
This is the second time, sir,

652
00:51:18,224 --> 00:51:22,494
you have been brought
before this bench.

653
00:51:22,562 --> 00:51:26,698
Though it is my earnest wish ever
to temper justice with mercy,

654
00:51:26,766 --> 00:51:29,968
your persistent dedication
to a life of crime

655
00:51:30,036 --> 00:51:33,738
is an abomination
before God and man.

656
00:51:33,806 --> 00:51:37,292
I therefore sentence you to hang
by the neck until you're dead.

657
00:51:37,360 --> 00:51:40,378
And may the Lord have
mercy on your soul.

658
00:51:41,413 --> 00:51:43,115
Court is adjourned.

659
00:51:52,158 --> 00:51:54,760
Thank you, Your Honor.

660
00:51:54,827 --> 00:51:56,495
Just the sentence we wanted.

661
00:51:56,562 --> 00:51:58,230
Was he guilty?

662
00:51:58,297 --> 00:51:59,597
Well, if he didn't do it,

663
00:51:59,665 --> 00:52:02,000
he's surely done something
to warrant a hanging.

664
00:52:02,068 --> 00:52:03,435
What man has not?

665
00:52:03,503 --> 00:52:04,802
Sorry?

666
00:52:07,773 --> 00:52:09,574
No matter. Come.

667
00:52:10,743 --> 00:52:12,527
Walk home with me.

668
00:52:15,448 --> 00:52:18,182
I have news for you, my friend.

669
00:52:18,250 --> 00:52:21,319
In order to shield her from
the evils of this world,

670
00:52:21,387 --> 00:52:24,756
I have decided to marry
my dear Johanna.

671
00:52:24,824 --> 00:52:27,258
Oh! Sir, happy news indeed.

672
00:52:27,326 --> 00:52:29,427
Strange though,

673
00:52:29,495 --> 00:52:31,396
when I offered myself to her,

674
00:52:31,464 --> 00:52:35,751
she showed a certain reluctance.

675
00:52:35,818 --> 00:52:37,536
Excuse me, my lord

676
00:52:37,603 --> 00:52:38,803
May I request, my lord

677
00:52:38,871 --> 00:52:41,305
Permission, my lord, to speak?

678
00:52:41,373 --> 00:52:43,658
Forgive me if I suggest, my lord

679
00:52:43,726 --> 00:52:46,127
You're looking less
than your best, my lord

680
00:52:46,195 --> 00:52:48,563
There's powder upon
your vest, my lord

681
00:52:48,631 --> 00:52:51,399
And stubble upon your cheek

682
00:52:54,036 --> 00:52:57,989
And ladies, my lord, are weak

683
00:52:58,757 --> 00:53:01,059
Stubble, you say?

684
00:53:04,363 --> 00:53:08,567
Perhaps I am a little
overhasty in the mornings.

685
00:53:08,634 --> 00:53:10,302
Fret not though, my lord

686
00:53:10,369 --> 00:53:11,436
I know a place, my lord

687
00:53:11,504 --> 00:53:14,072
A barber, my lord, of skill

688
00:53:14,140 --> 00:53:16,374
Thus armed with a
shaven face, my lord

689
00:53:16,442 --> 00:53:18,776
Some eau de cologne
to grace, my lord

690
00:53:18,844 --> 00:53:21,346
And musk to enhance
the chase, my lord

691
00:53:21,414 --> 00:53:24,316
You'll dazzle the girl until

692
00:53:25,217 --> 00:53:27,051
Until?

693
00:53:27,119 --> 00:53:31,340
She bows to your every will

694
00:53:32,375 --> 00:53:33,709
Barber?

695
00:53:34,977 --> 00:53:36,044
Take me to him.

696
00:53:36,111 --> 00:53:37,646
His name is Todd, my lord,

697
00:53:37,714 --> 00:53:40,582
and he is the very last
word in barbering.

698
00:53:47,690 --> 00:53:49,224
You ought to slow down a bit, lad.

699
00:53:49,291 --> 00:53:51,176
It'll go straight to your head.

700
00:53:51,244 --> 00:53:54,495
They used to give it to us in the
workhouse so as we could sleep.

701
00:53:54,563 --> 00:53:56,798
Not that you'd want to sleep
in that place, ma'am.

702
00:53:56,865 --> 00:53:59,384
Not with the things what
happen in the dark.

703
00:53:59,452 --> 00:54:00,701
That's nice, dear.

704
00:54:00,769 --> 00:54:02,570
Think I'll just pop in
on Mr. Todd for a tick.

705
00:54:02,638 --> 00:54:03,804
You all right, there?

706
00:54:03,872 --> 00:54:05,173
Leave the bottle.

707
00:54:10,462 --> 00:54:14,883
That lad is drinking me
out of house and home.

708
00:54:14,950 --> 00:54:17,852
How long till Pirelli gets back?

709
00:54:17,920 --> 00:54:19,905
He won't be back.

710
00:54:21,524 --> 00:54:23,425
Mr. T, you didn't.

711
00:54:34,603 --> 00:54:36,471
You're barking mad.

712
00:54:36,539 --> 00:54:38,990
Killing a man what
done you no harm.

713
00:54:39,058 --> 00:54:41,025
He recognized me from the old days.

714
00:54:41,093 --> 00:54:43,027
Tried to blackmail me.

715
00:54:44,363 --> 00:54:46,530
Half me earnings.

716
00:54:46,598 --> 00:54:50,235
Oh, well,
it's a different matter then.

717
00:54:50,302 --> 00:54:53,822
For a moment there, I thought
you'd lost your marbles.

718
00:54:56,859 --> 00:54:58,526
All that blood.

719
00:55:00,062 --> 00:55:01,513
Poor bugger.

720
00:55:02,348 --> 00:55:03,748
Oh, well.

721
00:55:12,124 --> 00:55:14,559
Well, waste not, want not.

722
00:55:16,161 --> 00:55:19,463
So, what are we gonna
do about the boy then?

723
00:55:20,966 --> 00:55:23,317
Send him up.

724
00:55:23,385 --> 00:55:26,388
Oh, we don't need to worry about him.
He's a simple thing.

725
00:55:26,455 --> 00:55:28,039
Send him up!

726
00:55:30,909 --> 00:55:35,447
Now, Mr. T, surely one's
enough for today.

727
00:55:35,514 --> 00:55:39,050
Besides, I was thinking of hiring
the lad to help me run the shop.

728
00:55:39,118 --> 00:55:42,119
Your poor knees aren't
what they used to be.

729
00:55:42,888 --> 00:55:44,255
All right.

730
00:55:46,342 --> 00:55:48,776
Course, we're gonna have
to stock up on the gin.

731
00:55:48,844 --> 00:55:50,912
Boy drinks like a sailor.

732
00:55:54,916 --> 00:55:56,233
The Judge.

733
00:55:59,722 --> 00:56:01,022
Get out.

734
00:56:03,075 --> 00:56:04,375
Get out!

735
00:56:20,726 --> 00:56:22,377
Mr. Todd?

736
00:56:23,245 --> 00:56:25,980
At your service.

737
00:56:26,048 --> 00:56:29,217
An honor to receive
your patronage, my lord.

738
00:56:30,552 --> 00:56:32,404
You know me, sir?

739
00:56:32,471 --> 00:56:37,825
Who in this wide world does not
know the great Judge Turpin?

740
00:56:44,400 --> 00:56:46,351
These premises are
hardly prepossessing,

741
00:56:46,419 --> 00:56:48,286
and yet the Beadle tells me

742
00:56:48,354 --> 00:56:52,857
you're the most accomplished of
all the barbers in the city.

743
00:56:52,925 --> 00:56:55,327
That is gracious of him, sir.

744
00:56:56,362 --> 00:56:59,497
What may I do for you today, sir?

745
00:56:59,565 --> 00:57:02,400
A stylish trimming of the hair?

746
00:57:02,468 --> 00:57:04,485
Soothing skin massage?

747
00:57:04,554 --> 00:57:07,404
Sit, sir. Sit.

748
00:57:07,472 --> 00:57:10,258
You see, sir,
a man infatuate with love

749
00:57:10,325 --> 00:57:12,727
Her ardent and eager slave

750
00:57:12,795 --> 00:57:15,246
So fetch the pomade
and pumice stone

751
00:57:15,313 --> 00:57:17,482
And lend me a more seductive tone

752
00:57:17,550 --> 00:57:20,051
A sprinkling perhaps
of French cologne

753
00:57:20,118 --> 00:57:22,036
But first, sir, I think

754
00:57:23,088 --> 00:57:25,690
A shave

755
00:57:27,425 --> 00:57:30,561
The closest I ever gave

756
00:57:35,167 --> 00:57:37,502
You're in a merry
mood today, Mr. Todd.

757
00:57:37,569 --> 00:57:40,304
'Tis your delight,
sir, catching fire

758
00:57:40,372 --> 00:57:43,024
From one man to the next

759
00:57:43,091 --> 00:57:45,442
'Tis true, sir,
love can still inspire

760
00:57:45,510 --> 00:57:47,945
The blood to pound
the heart leap higher

761
00:57:48,013 --> 00:57:49,446
What more
What more

762
00:57:49,514 --> 00:57:51,749
Can man require than love, sir
Can man require

763
00:57:51,817 --> 00:57:52,968
More than love, sir

764
00:57:53,102 --> 00:57:54,385
What, sir?
Women

765
00:57:54,453 --> 00:57:55,719
Yes, women

766
00:57:55,787 --> 00:57:56,988
Pretty women

767
00:58:28,070 --> 00:58:32,273
Now then, my friend

768
00:58:33,342 --> 00:58:37,245
Now to your purpose

769
00:58:38,214 --> 00:58:42,750
Patience, enjoy it

770
00:58:42,818 --> 00:58:47,155
Revenge can't be taken in haste

771
00:58:47,223 --> 00:58:48,556
Make haste, and if we wed

772
00:58:48,624 --> 00:58:49,724
You'll be commended, sir

773
00:58:49,791 --> 00:58:51,192
My lord

774
00:58:53,629 --> 00:58:56,097
And who, may it be said
ls your intended, sir?

775
00:58:56,165 --> 00:58:58,699
My ward

776
00:58:59,952 --> 00:59:02,287
A pretty little rosebud.

777
00:59:02,354 --> 00:59:04,289
Pretty as her mother?

778
00:59:05,324 --> 00:59:07,925
What? What was that?

779
00:59:07,993 --> 00:59:12,313
Nothing, sir. Nothing.
May we proceed?

780
00:59:14,016 --> 00:59:16,150
Pretty women

781
00:59:16,218 --> 00:59:18,520
Fascinating

782
00:59:18,587 --> 00:59:20,822
Sipping coffee

783
00:59:21,456 --> 00:59:23,758
Dancing

784
00:59:23,826 --> 00:59:26,628
Pretty women!

785
00:59:26,695 --> 00:59:29,096
Are a wonder

786
00:59:29,164 --> 00:59:31,666
Pretty women

787
00:59:34,436 --> 00:59:39,340
Sitting in the window or

788
00:59:39,408 --> 00:59:44,345
Standing on the stair

789
00:59:44,413 --> 00:59:46,380
Something in them

790
00:59:47,049 --> 00:59:53,421
Cheers the air

791
00:59:54,690 --> 00:59:56,791
Pretty women

792
00:59:57,509 --> 00:59:59,827
Silhouetted

793
00:59:59,895 --> 01:00:02,313
Stay within you

794
01:00:02,380 --> 01:00:05,032
Glancing!

795
01:00:05,100 --> 01:00:07,619
Stay forever

796
01:00:07,621 --> 01:00:10,138
Breathing lightly

797
01:00:10,205 --> 01:00:12,340
Pretty women

798
01:00:12,408 --> 01:00:14,759
Pretty women

799
01:00:14,827 --> 01:00:19,714
Blowing out their candles or
Blowing out their candles or

800
01:00:19,781 --> 01:00:21,416
Combing out their hair

801
01:00:21,650 --> 01:00:23,100
Combing out their hair

802
01:00:23,168 --> 01:00:24,902
Then they leave

803
01:00:24,970 --> 01:00:28,389
Even when they leave...
Even when they leave you and vanish...

804
01:00:28,456 --> 01:00:31,359
...they still...
...they somehow can still remain...

805
01:00:31,427 --> 01:00:34,295
...are there, they're there

806
01:00:34,363 --> 01:00:36,931
...there with you

807
01:00:36,999 --> 01:00:38,383
Pretty women

808
01:00:38,450 --> 01:00:39,730
At their mirrors
In their gardens

809
01:00:39,768 --> 01:00:41,335
Letter-writing
Flower-picking

810
01:00:41,403 --> 01:00:42,470
Weather-watching

811
01:00:42,538 --> 01:00:47,391
How they make a man sing

812
01:00:47,560 --> 01:00:50,027
Proof of heaven

813
01:00:50,095 --> 01:00:52,463
