01:17:13,260 --> 01:17:14,894
Quick, sir, run and tell

1081
01:17:14,961 --> 01:17:17,764
Warn them all of the witch's spell
There it is, there it is, the unholy smell

1082
01:17:17,831 --> 01:17:20,316
Tell it to the Beadle and police as well
Tell them! Tell them

1083
01:17:20,383 --> 01:17:24,153
Help, fiend! City on fire!

1084
01:17:24,221 --> 01:17:27,673
City on fire

1085
01:17:27,741 --> 01:17:29,542
Mischief. Mischief.

1086
01:17:39,336 --> 01:17:42,905
And though I'll
think of you, I guess

1087
01:17:42,973 --> 01:17:45,808
Until the day I die

1088
01:17:45,876 --> 01:17:49,161
I think I miss you less and less

1089
01:17:49,263 --> 01:17:51,614
As every day goes by

1090
01:17:51,682 --> 01:17:55,050
Johanna

1091
01:17:55,118 --> 01:17:58,387
Johanna

1092
01:17:58,455 --> 01:18:02,041
And you'd be beautiful and pale

1093
01:18:02,109 --> 01:18:04,994
And look too much like her

1094
01:18:05,062 --> 01:18:08,414
If only angels could prevail

1095
01:18:08,482 --> 01:18:10,716
We'd be the way we were

1096
01:18:10,784 --> 01:18:14,220
Johanna

1097
01:18:14,288 --> 01:18:17,690
I feel you, Johanna

1098
01:18:17,758 --> 01:18:20,827
Wake up, Johanna

1099
01:18:20,894 --> 01:18:24,029
Another bright red day

1100
01:18:24,097 --> 01:18:30,837
We learn, Johanna, to say

1101
01:18:32,473 --> 01:18:37,626
Goodbye

1102
01:18:37,694 --> 01:18:44,283
I'll steal

1103
01:18:44,351 --> 01:18:49,271
You

1104
01:19:26,610 --> 01:19:28,076
Ladies and gentlemen

1105
01:19:28,144 --> 01:19:30,579
May I have your
attention, please?

1106
01:19:31,948 --> 01:19:33,982
Are your nostrils a-quiver
and tingling as well

1107
01:19:34,050 --> 01:19:37,152
At that delicate
luscious ambrosial smell?

1108
01:19:37,220 --> 01:19:39,355
Yes, they are, I can tell

1109
01:19:39,423 --> 01:19:41,056
Well, ladies and gentlemen

1110
01:19:41,124 --> 01:19:43,292
That aroma enriching the breeze

1111
01:19:43,360 --> 01:19:45,244
ls like nothing compared
to its succulent source

1112
01:19:45,311 --> 01:19:49,098
As the gourmets among you
will tell you, of course

1113
01:19:49,166 --> 01:19:50,600
Ladies and gentlemen

1114
01:19:50,668 --> 01:19:54,970
You can't imagine
the rapture in store

1115
01:19:55,038 --> 01:19:57,373
Just inside of this door!

1116
01:20:01,612 --> 01:20:05,114
There you'll sample
Mrs. Lovett's meat pies

1117
01:20:05,182 --> 01:20:06,982
Savory and sweet pies

1118
01:20:07,050 --> 01:20:08,685
As you'll see

1119
01:20:08,752 --> 01:20:12,254
You who eat pies
Mrs. Lovett's meat pies

1120
01:20:12,323 --> 01:20:15,858
Conjure up the treat
pies used to be!

1121
01:20:19,563 --> 01:20:21,331
Toby!
coming!

1122
01:20:22,366 --> 01:20:24,133
Ale there!
Right, ma'am!

1123
01:20:24,201 --> 01:20:25,635
Quick, now!

1124
01:20:26,837 --> 01:20:28,738
Nice to see you, dearie

1125
01:20:28,806 --> 01:20:30,506
How have you been keeping?

1126
01:20:30,574 --> 01:20:32,308
Cor, me bones is weary

1127
01:20:32,376 --> 01:20:34,210
Toby! One for the gentleman

1128
01:20:34,277 --> 01:20:35,911
Hear the birdies cheeping

1129
01:20:35,979 --> 01:20:37,880
Helps to keep it cheery

1130
01:20:37,948 --> 01:20:41,417
Toby! Throw the old woman out!

1131
01:20:41,485 --> 01:20:43,519
What's my secret?

1132
01:20:43,587 --> 01:20:45,321
Frankly, dear, forgive my candor

1133
01:20:45,389 --> 01:20:47,189
Family secret

1134
01:20:47,257 --> 01:20:48,891
All to do with herbs

1135
01:20:48,959 --> 01:20:52,462
Things like being careful
with your coriander

1136
01:20:52,529 --> 01:20:55,564
That's what makes
the gravy grander!

1137
01:21:05,125 --> 01:21:07,726
Eat them slow and feel the crust

1138
01:21:07,794 --> 01:21:08,961
How thin she rolled it

1139
01:21:09,029 --> 01:21:12,431
Eat them slow 'cause
every one's a prize!

1140
01:21:12,498 --> 01:21:15,968
Eat them slow 'cause that's
the lot and now we've sold it!

1141
01:21:16,036 --> 01:21:17,336
Come again tomorrow!

1142
01:21:17,403 --> 01:21:18,737
Hold it!

1143
01:21:19,706 --> 01:21:21,807
Bless my eyes!

1144
01:21:23,409 --> 01:21:25,377
Fresh supplies!

1145
01:21:25,445 --> 01:21:26,846
- How about it, dearie?
- Is that a pie...

1146
01:21:26,913 --> 01:21:28,747
Be here in a twinkling!
...fit for a king

1147
01:21:28,815 --> 01:21:30,415
Just confirms me theory, Toby!

1148
01:21:30,483 --> 01:21:32,751
A wondrous sweet and most
delectable thing? God watches over us

1149
01:21:32,819 --> 01:21:35,980
Didn't have an inkling, positively eerie
You see, ma'am why there's no meat pie

1150
01:21:36,022 --> 01:21:38,724
Toby! Throw the old woman out!

1151
01:21:46,766 --> 01:21:49,601
Still got to keep an eye on
the household expenditure.

1152
01:21:50,237 --> 01:21:51,804
Mmm.

1153
01:21:51,872 --> 01:21:54,352
Which isn't to say we couldn't
get some nice taxidermy animals,

1154
01:21:54,391 --> 01:21:56,692
bring a touch of
gentility to the place.

1155
01:21:56,760 --> 01:21:59,361
You know, a boar's head or two?

1156
01:22:00,597 --> 01:22:02,698
Mr. T? You listening to me?

1157
01:22:03,450 --> 01:22:04,967
Of course.

1158
01:22:05,034 --> 01:22:07,403
Then what did I just say?

1159
01:22:07,471 --> 01:22:09,989
There must be a way to the Judge.

1160
01:22:10,056 --> 01:22:14,142
Judge. Always harping
on the bloody old judge.

1161
01:22:14,210 --> 01:22:16,479
We got a nice respectable
business now.

1162
01:22:16,546 --> 01:22:18,447
Money coming in regular-like.

1163
01:22:18,515 --> 01:22:20,349
And since we're careful
to pick and choose,

1164
01:22:20,416 --> 01:22:24,536
strangers, people who won't be
missed, who's gonna catch on?

1165
01:22:26,139 --> 01:22:28,306
Mr. Todd, I'm so happy

1166
01:22:28,374 --> 01:22:30,642
I could eat you up,
I really could

1167
01:22:30,827 --> 01:22:32,244
You know what I'd
like to do, Mr. Todd?

1168
01:22:32,312 --> 01:22:34,113
What I dream?

1169
01:22:34,181 --> 01:22:35,465
If the business stays as good

1170
01:22:35,532 --> 01:22:38,167
Where I'd really like to go

1171
01:22:38,234 --> 01:22:40,319
In a year or so?

1172
01:22:40,387 --> 01:22:42,605
Don't you want to know?

1173
01:22:42,672 --> 01:22:43,990
Of course.

1174
01:22:44,057 --> 01:22:45,791
Do you really want to know?

1175
01:22:45,859 --> 01:22:47,743
Yes, I do.

1176
01:23:02,492 --> 01:23:03,860
By the sea, Mr. Todd

1177
01:23:03,927 --> 01:23:05,544
That's the life I'll covet

1178
01:23:05,611 --> 01:23:07,046
By the sea, Mr. Todd

1179
01:23:07,114 --> 01:23:08,480
Oh, I know you'd love it

1180
01:23:08,548 --> 01:23:11,083
You and me, Mr. T,
we could be alone

1181
01:23:11,151 --> 01:23:13,619
In a house what we'd almost own

1182
01:23:13,686 --> 01:23:15,321
Down by the sea

1183
01:23:15,389 --> 01:23:16,956
Anything you say

1184
01:23:17,024 --> 01:23:19,859
Wouldn't that be smashing?

1185
01:23:20,793 --> 01:23:22,277
Think how snug it'll be

1186
01:23:22,345 --> 01:23:23,879
Underneath our flannel

1187
01:23:23,947 --> 01:23:25,280
When it's just you and me

1188
01:23:25,348 --> 01:23:27,082
And the English Channel

1189
01:23:27,150 --> 01:23:28,401
In our cozy retreat

1190
01:23:28,468 --> 01:23:29,868
Kept all neat and tidy

1191
01:23:29,937 --> 01:23:33,005
We'll have chums
over every Friday

1192
01:23:33,073 --> 01:23:35,274
By the sea

1193
01:23:35,309 --> 01:23:41,497
Don't you love the
weather by the sea?

1194
01:23:41,698 --> 01:23:45,034
We'll grow old together

1195
01:23:45,102 --> 01:23:47,603
By the seaside

1196
01:23:47,671 --> 01:23:49,772
By the beautiful sea

1197
01:23:54,545 --> 01:24:00,783
It'll be so quiet that who'll
come by it except a seagull?

1198
01:24:00,851 --> 01:24:06,688
We shouldn't try it though,
till it's legal for two!

1199
01:24:06,756 --> 01:24:09,775
But a seaside wedding
could be devised

1200
01:24:09,842 --> 01:24:12,811
Me rumpled bedding legitimized

1201
01:24:13,013 --> 01:24:15,698
Me eyelids'll flutter,
I'll turn into butter

1202
01:24:15,766 --> 01:24:18,517
The moment I mutter "I do!"

1203
01:24:18,584 --> 01:24:22,321
Will you take this woman to
be your lawfully wedded wife?

1204
01:24:26,393 --> 01:24:28,377
You may kiss your bride.

1205
01:24:40,807 --> 01:24:43,225
Down by the sea

1206
01:24:43,293 --> 01:24:46,796
Married nice and proper

1207
01:24:46,863 --> 01:24:49,315
By the sea

1208
01:24:49,382 --> 01:24:52,518
Bring along your chopper

1209
01:24:52,586 --> 01:24:55,454
To the seaside

1210
01:24:55,522 --> 01:24:59,157
By the beautiful sea

1211
01:25:17,277 --> 01:25:19,929
I brought you some breakfast, dear.

1212
01:25:23,783 --> 01:25:26,835
Mr. T? Can I ask you a question?

1213
01:25:28,004 --> 01:25:29,137
What?

1214
01:25:30,173 --> 01:25:32,508
What did your Lucy look like?

1215
01:25:35,412 --> 01:25:37,713
Can't really remember, can you?

1216
01:25:39,015 --> 01:25:41,032
She had yellow hair.

1217
01:25:43,020 --> 01:25:45,871
You gotta leave this
all behind, you know.

1218
01:25:47,624 --> 01:25:49,257
She's gone.

1219
01:25:50,994 --> 01:25:53,212
Life is for the alive, my dear.

1220
01:25:54,313 --> 01:25:57,082
We could have a life, us two.

1221
01:25:57,150 --> 01:25:59,218
Maybe not like I dreamed.

1222
01:26:00,253 --> 01:26:02,454
Maybe not like you remember.

1223
01:26:03,489 --> 01:26:05,323
But we could get by.

1224
01:26:13,899 --> 01:26:16,735
Mr. Todd! Mrs. Lovett, ma'am?

1225
01:26:16,802 --> 01:26:18,137
What is it, Anthony?

1226
01:26:18,205 --> 01:26:20,155
He has her locked in a madhouse.

1227
01:26:20,873 --> 01:26:22,058
Johanna.

1228
01:26:22,125 --> 01:26:25,211
Fogg's Asylum. I've circled
the place a dozen times.

1229
01:26:25,278 --> 01:26:27,580
There's no way in. It's a fortress.

1230
01:26:28,548 --> 01:26:30,015
I've got him.

1231
01:26:30,083 --> 01:26:31,567
Mr. Todd?

1232
01:26:32,703 --> 01:26:34,369
We've got her.

1233
01:26:35,672 --> 01:26:39,641
Where do you suppose all the wigmakers
in London go to obtain their hair?

1234
01:26:40,476 --> 01:26:42,444
Bedlam.

1235
01:26:42,512 --> 01:26:44,330
They get it from the
lunatics at Bedlam.

1236
01:26:44,397 --> 01:26:46,348
I don't understand.

1237
01:26:47,817 --> 01:26:50,819
We shall set you up as a
wigmaker's apprentice.

1238
01:26:50,971 --> 01:26:52,587
That'll gain you access.

1239
01:26:52,655 --> 01:26:54,056
And then you take her.

1240
01:26:54,807 --> 01:26:56,492
Go, quickly, go!

1241
01:26:57,961 --> 01:26:59,428
Fetch the boy.

1242
01:26:59,496 --> 01:27:02,881
Don't you think you should
leave the boy behind?

1243
01:27:17,397 --> 01:27:20,166
Toby. Mr. Todd needs you.

1244
01:27:20,233 --> 01:27:21,500
Yes, ma'am.

1245
01:27:34,480 --> 01:27:35,848
Mr. T?

1246
01:27:38,384 --> 01:27:40,385
Do you know where
the Old Bailey is?

1247
01:27:40,453 --> 01:27:42,387
Yes, sir.
Not that I ever been there.

1248
01:27:42,455 --> 01:27:44,523
Take this there.

1249
01:27:44,591 --> 01:27:46,692
Seek out a Judge Turpin.
Repeat that.

1250
01:27:46,760 --> 01:27:49,161
Go to Old Bailey.
Find Judge Turpin.

1251
01:27:49,229 --> 01:27:50,762
You put that into his hands.

1252
01:27:50,830 --> 01:27:52,648
Only to him, you understand?

1253
01:27:52,716 --> 01:27:54,033
Yes, sir.

1254
01:27:54,100 --> 01:27:56,302
And while I'm out, do you mind if
I stop by the grocer just to pick...

1255
01:27:56,369 --> 01:27:59,037
No. You're not to stop,
you're not to speak.

1256
01:27:59,105 --> 01:28:00,406
You're to deliver the letter.

1257
01:28:00,473 --> 01:28:01,740
Do you understand?

1258
01:28:01,808 --> 01:28:03,375
Yes, sir.

1259
01:28:33,489 --> 01:28:34,990
Where you been, lad?

1260
01:28:35,058 --> 01:28:37,393
We had quite the
rush at dinner time.

1261
01:28:37,460 --> 01:28:39,844
Me poor bones is ready to drop.

1262
01:28:39,912 --> 01:28:42,180
Mr. Todd sent me on an errand.

1263
01:28:42,248 --> 01:28:43,381
And on the way back,

1264
01:28:43,450 --> 01:28:46,251
I went by the workhouse,
just to take a look.

1265
01:28:46,319 --> 01:28:50,155
And I was thinking, but for
you, I'd be there now.

1266
01:28:51,223 --> 01:28:53,091
Or someplace worse.

1267
01:28:53,159 --> 01:28:55,143
Seems like the good
Lord sent you for me.

1268
01:28:55,211 --> 01:28:58,630
Oh, love,
I feel quite the same way.

1269
01:28:58,698 --> 01:29:00,633
Listen to me, please.

1270
01:29:00,700 --> 01:29:02,984
You know there's nothing
I wouldn't do for you.

1271
01:29:03,052 --> 01:29:06,238
Say, if there were someone around,

1272
01:29:07,090 --> 01:29:09,391
someone bad?

1273
01:29:09,458 --> 01:29:12,076
Only you didn't know it.

1274
01:29:12,144 --> 01:29:13,228
What is this?

1275
01:29:13,296 --> 01:29:15,130
What are you talking about?

1276
01:29:17,833 --> 01:29:20,786
Nothing's gonna harm you

1277
01:29:20,854 --> 01:29:24,390
Not while I'm around

1278
01:29:25,792 --> 01:29:27,493
Nothing's gonna harm you

1279
01:29:27,560 --> 01:29:31,396
No, sir, not while I'm around

1280
01:29:31,464 --> 01:29:32,914
What do you mean "someone bad"?

1281
01:29:32,982 --> 01:29:40,405
Demons are prowling
everywhere nowadays

1282
01:29:40,407 --> 01:29:44,075
I'll send them howling,
I don't care

1283
01:29:44,143 --> 01:29:47,963
I got ways

1284
01:29:48,031 --> 01:29:50,915
Hush, darling,
there's no need for this.

1285
01:29:52,685 --> 01:29:55,337
No one's gonna hurt you

1286
01:29:55,405 --> 01:29:59,090
No one's gonna dare

1287
01:30:00,309 --> 01:30:02,227
Others can desert you

1288
01:30:02,294 --> 01:30:06,648
Not to worry,
whistle, I'll be there

1289
01:30:06,715 --> 01:30:08,650
Demons will charm you

1290
01:30:08,718 --> 01:30:10,602
With a smile

1291
01:30:10,670 --> 01:30:16,458
For a while, but in time

1292
01:30:16,526 --> 01:30:19,328
Nothing can harm you

1293
01:30:20,446 --> 01:30:25,667
Not while I'm around

1294
01:30:29,255 --> 01:30:31,539
That's nice, dear.

1295
01:30:31,607 --> 01:30:33,942
Now, what is all this foolishness?

1296
01:30:34,010 --> 01:30:36,912
What are you talking about?

1297
01:30:36,980 --> 01:30:41,750
Little things that I've been
thinking about Mr. Todd.

1298
01:30:41,818 --> 01:30:44,019
Not to worry, not to worry

1299
01:30:44,087 --> 01:30:47,172
I may not be smart,
but I ain't dumb

1300
01:30:48,107 --> 01:30:50,442
I can do it, put me to it

1301
01:30:50,510 --> 01:30:53,312
Show me something I can overcome

1302
01:30:54,581 --> 01:30:58,650
Not to worry, ma'am

1303
01:31:01,403 --> 01:31:03,805
Being close and being clever

1304
01:31:03,873 --> 01:31:05,941
Ain't like being true

1305
01:31:06,959 --> 01:31:09,861
I don't need to, I won't never

1306
01:31:09,929 --> 01:31:12,547
Hide a thing from you

1307
01:31:12,615 --> 01:31:16,067
Like some

1308
01:31:17,871 --> 01:31:22,107
Now, Toby, dear, haven't we had
enough of this foolish chatter?

1309
01:31:22,175 --> 01:31:23,459
Here.

1310
01:31:23,526 --> 01:31:28,730
How about I give you
a nice shiny new penny

1311
01:31:28,798 --> 01:31:31,700
and you go get us some toffees?

1312
01:31:33,870 --> 01:31:35,587
That's Signor Pirelli's purse!

1313
01:31:35,654 --> 01:31:38,523
No, it's not. Just something
Mr. T gave me for my birthday.

1314
01:31:38,591 --> 01:31:40,525
That proves it! We gotta go, ma'am.

1315
01:31:40,593 --> 01:31:42,794
We gotta find the Beadle
and get the law here!

1316
01:31:42,861 --> 01:31:45,730
Toby. Hush, lad,
you're not going anywhere.

1317
01:31:45,798 --> 01:31:49,067
You just sit here, nice
and quiet, next to me.

1318
01:31:49,135 --> 01:31:50,768
That's right, right.

1319
01:31:53,706 --> 01:31:56,475
How could you think such
a thing of Mr. Todd?

1320
01:31:56,543 --> 01:31:59,043
He's been so good to us.

1321
01:32:03,299 --> 01:32:06,368
Nothing's gonna harm you

1322
01:32:06,435 --> 01:32:09,838
Not while I'm around

1323
01:32:11,557 --> 01:32:14,660
Nothing's gonna harm you, darling

1324
01:32:14,727 --> 01:32:18,247
Not while I'm around

1325
01:32:18,314 --> 01:32:22,083
Demons'll charm you with a smile

1326
01:32:22,151 --> 01:32:24,018
For a while

1327
01:32:24,086 --> 01:32:27,305
But in time

1328
01:32:27,373 --> 01:32:31,442
Nothing's gonna harm you

1329
01:32:31,510 --> 01:32:37,198
Not while I'm around

1330
01:32:40,836 --> 01:32:43,905
Funny we should be having
this little chat right now.

1331
01:32:43,973 --> 01:32:45,641
'Cause I was just thinking...

1332
01:32:47,009 --> 01:32:48,826
You know how you've always
fancied coming into

1333
01:32:48,852 --> 01:32:51,421
the bake house with me
to help make the pies?

1334
01:32:51,464 --> 01:32:53,081
Yes, ma'am.

1335
01:32:53,083 --> 01:32:57,552
Well, no time like the present, eh?

1336
01:33:17,289 --> 01:33:20,759
I feel bad for you, going up
and down all these stairs.

1337
01:33:20,827 --> 01:33:22,728
Well, that'll be your job now.

1338
01:33:22,795 --> 01:33:24,662
Yes, ma'am.

1339
01:33:29,068 --> 01:33:31,320
Quite a stink, ain't there?

1340
01:33:35,024 --> 01:33:36,391
You see those grates?

1341
01:33:36,459 --> 01:33:39,294
They go right down to the
sewers, and the smells come up.

1342
01:33:39,362 --> 01:33:41,797
Always a few rats gone
home to Jesus down there.

1343
01:33:41,865 --> 01:33:43,832
Now, this'll be the bake oven.

1344
01:33:43,900 --> 01:33:45,801
Three dozen at a time.

1345
01:33:45,869 --> 01:33:48,670
Always be sure the door is
closed properly, like this.

1346
01:33:48,738 --> 01:33:50,539
Door's closed properly.

1347
01:33:50,607 --> 01:33:52,875
This is a grinder.

1348
01:33:52,942 --> 01:33:56,311
Pop in the meat.
Give it a good grind.

1349
01:33:59,599 --> 01:34:01,332
Pops out there.

1350
01:34:03,202 --> 01:34:04,603
You try.

1351
01:34:06,272 --> 01:34:07,539
Good grind.

1352
01:34:09,141 --> 01:34:10,908
Comes out there.

1353
01:34:12,878 --> 01:34:14,379
That's my boy.

1354
01:34:14,447 --> 01:34:17,181
I'm just gonna pop upstairs,
back in two shakes, all right?

1355
01:34:17,250 --> 01:34:20,518
You mind if I have
a pie while I wait?

1356
01:34:20,586 --> 01:34:22,604
As many as you like, son.

1357
01:34:35,318 --> 01:34:36,801
Yes, sir, I agree.

1358
01:34:36,869 --> 01:34:38,503
It would be to our mutual interest

1359
01:34:38,571 --> 01:34:42,407
to come to some arrangement in
regard to my poor children's hair.

1360
01:34:42,475 --> 01:34:43,941
Brunettes.

1361
01:34:45,478 --> 01:34:47,011
Redheads.

1362
01:34:49,682 --> 01:34:52,183
I keep the blondes in here.

1363
01:34:52,251 --> 01:34:54,886
It was yellow hair you
was looking for, sir?

1364
01:34:54,937 --> 01:34:56,321
Yes.

1365
01:35:05,731 --> 01:35:06,731
Hey!

1366
01:35:27,353 --> 01:35:29,387
That one there has
the shade I need.

1367
01:35:29,455 --> 01:35:31,422
Come, child.

1368
01:35:38,130 --> 01:35:41,666
Smile for the gentleman and
you shall have a sweetie.

1369
01:35:43,685 --> 01:35:45,937
Now, where shall I cut?

1370
01:35:47,306 --> 01:35:50,708
Not another word, Mr. Fogg,
or it will be your last.

1371
01:35:52,611 --> 01:35:57,515
Now, I leave you to the
mercy of your children.

1372
01:36:07,910 --> 01:36:09,544
I got him locked in.

1373
01:36:09,612 --> 01:36:11,246
But if he escapes,
he'll go to the law.

1374
01:36:11,314 --> 01:36:12,447
Then he won't escape.

1375
01:36:12,515 --> 01:36:13,582
I don't know, Mr. Todd.

1376
01:36:13,649 --> 01:36:15,950
<i>The Judge“ be here soon.</i>

1377
01:36:17,487 --> 01:36:20,355
'Souse me, sir. Gave me a fright.

1378
01:36:20,423 --> 01:36:22,124
Not my intention, good madam.

1379
01:36:22,191 --> 01:36:24,092
I assure you.

1380
01:36:24,160 --> 01:36:27,812
Though I am here on
official business.

1381
01:36:27,880 --> 01:36:30,515
You see, there's
been some complaints

1382
01:36:30,582 --> 01:36:33,184
about the stink from your chimney.

1383
01:36:33,252 --> 01:36:37,088
They say at night it is
something most foul.

1384
01:36:37,156 --> 01:36:40,292
Health regulations and the
general public welfare

1385
01:36:40,359 --> 01:36:42,360
naturally being my duty,

1386
01:36:42,362 --> 01:36:45,513
I'm afraid I'm gonna
have to take a look

1387
01:36:48,351 --> 01:36:50,084
at your bakehouse.

1388
01:36:51,503 --> 01:36:52,987
Of course, sir.

1389
01:36:53,055 --> 01:36:55,457
But first, why don't
you come upstairs?

1390
01:36:55,525 --> 01:36:57,325
Let me pamper you.

1391
01:36:58,494 --> 01:37:01,463
Much as I do appreciate
tonsorial doormen

1392
01:37:01,531 --> 01:37:04,032
I really ought to see to my
official obligations first.

1393
01:37:04,099 --> 01:37:06,134
I completely understand.

1394
01:37:09,472 --> 01:37:14,092
If you'll indulge me, sir,
what is that exotic aroma?

1395
01:37:17,013 --> 01:37:20,081
Me secret, is a touch of ambergris.

1396
01:37:21,434 --> 01:37:24,135
Dare I offer you something
a tad more appropriate

1397
01:37:24,202 --> 01:37:26,638
for a gentleman of your standing?

1398
01:37:26,705 --> 01:37:29,674
The ladies will greatly
appreciate it, sir.

1399
01:37:32,495 --> 01:37:35,797
You're the expert in these matters.

1400
01:37:35,865 --> 01:37:37,832
Only take a moment.

1401
01:37:41,937 --> 01:37:44,472
Would you like a bit
of bay rum, sir?

1402
01:37:44,540 --> 01:37:46,841
Bay rum is very bracing.

1403
01:38:52,658 --> 01:38:56,394
Let me out! Please, let me out!

1404
01:38:59,064 --> 01:39:00,732
Let me out!

1405
01:39:18,334 --> 01:39:19,534
Toby?

1406
01:39:21,303 --> 01:39:22,903
Where is he?

1407
01:39:26,975 --> 01:39:31,879
Toby, where are you, love?

1408
01:39:33,949 --> 01:39:35,250
Toby?

1409
01:39:39,188 --> 01:39:42,857
Nothing's gonna harm you

1410
01:39:42,924 --> 01:39:46,194
Not while I'm around

1411
01:39:46,262 --> 01:39:47,562
Toby?

1412
01:39:49,365 --> 01:39:51,666
Where are you hiding?

1413
01:39:53,169 --> 01:39:54,369
Toby?

1414
01:39:55,538 --> 01:39:58,773
Nothing's gonna harm you, darling

1415
01:40:01,243 --> 01:40:03,878
Not while I'm around

1416
01:40:07,883 --> 01:40:09,184
Toby?

1417
01:40:11,287 --> 01:40:12,753
Mr. Todd!

1418
01:40:14,756 --> 01:40:16,391
You wait for him here.

1419
01:40:16,458 --> 01:40:19,994
I'll return with a coach
in less than half an hour.

1420
01:40:20,062 --> 01:40:23,431
Don't worry.
No one'll recognize you.

1421
01:40:23,515 --> 01:40:25,483
You're safe now.

1422
01:40:25,550 --> 01:40:27,251
Safe?

1423
01:40:27,319 --> 01:40:30,939
So, we run away and then
all our dreams come true?

1424
01:40:31,490 --> 01:40:33,959
I hope so.

1425
01:40:34,026 --> 01:40:37,278
I've never had dreams.
Only nightmares.

1426
01:40:38,164 --> 01:40:40,364
Johanna,

1427
01:40:40,432 --> 01:40:43,868
when we're free of this place
all the ghosts will go away.

1428
01:40:43,936 --> 01:40:47,372
No, Anthony. They never go away.

1429
01:40:48,373 --> 01:40:50,041
I'll be right back to you.

1430
01:40:50,109 --> 01:40:51,893
Half an hour and we'll be free.

1431
01:41:27,546 --> 01:41:30,214
Beadle! Beadle!

1432
01:41:31,366 --> 01:41:36,170
No good hiding, I saw you

1433
01:41:36,238 --> 01:41:38,740
Are you in there still, Beadle?

1434
01:41:38,808 --> 01:41:41,242
Beadle?

1435
01:41:41,310 --> 01:41:44,145
Beadle, dear Beadle?

1436
01:41:46,248 --> 01:41:49,417
Beadle deedle deedle
deedle deedle dumpling

1437
01:41:49,485 --> 01:41:51,452
Beadle dumpling...

1438
01:41:51,520 --> 01:41:54,322
Dee dee dee dee dee dee

1439
01:41:58,694 --> 01:42:00,228
Who are you?

1440
01:42:00,295 --> 01:42:01,863
What are you doing here?

1441
01:42:03,982 --> 01:42:05,517
Evil is here, sir.

1442
01:42:05,584 --> 01:42:08,453
The stink of evil,
from below, from her!

1443
01:42:08,521 --> 01:42:10,221
Oh, she's the Devil's wife.

1444
01:42:10,289 --> 01:42:12,023
Beware her, sir.

1445
01:42:12,091 --> 01:42:14,059
She with no pity in her heart.

1446
01:42:16,278 --> 01:42:19,180
Don't I know you, mister?

1447
01:42:19,248 --> 01:42:20,748
Mr. Todd?

1448
01:42:32,093 --> 01:42:33,577
Where is she?

1449
01:42:35,147 --> 01:42:38,666
Below, Your Honor.
With my neighbor.

1450
01:42:38,734 --> 01:42:42,337
Thank heavens the sailor
did not molest her.

1451
01:42:42,404 --> 01:42:47,007
Thank heavens, too, she has
seen the error of her ways.

1452
01:42:47,843 --> 01:42:49,127
She has?

1453
01:42:49,211 --> 01:42:51,012
Oh, yes.

1454
01:42:51,080 --> 01:42:53,465
Your lesson was well-learned.

1455
01:42:53,532 --> 01:42:55,467
She speaks only of you.

1456
01:42:55,534 --> 01:42:57,535
Longing for forgiveness.

1457
01:42:59,371 --> 01:43:01,489
Then she shall have it.

1458
01:43:02,508 --> 01:43:04,509
She'll be here soon, you say?

1459
01:43:04,577 --> 01:43:06,510
Yes.

1460
01:43:06,578 --> 01:43:08,513
Excellent, my friend.

1461
01:43:10,482 --> 01:43:12,216
How about a shave?

1462
01:43:13,619 --> 01:43:15,503
Sit, sir. Sit.

1463
01:43:18,473 --> 01:43:23,110
Oh, pretty women

1464
01:43:23,178 --> 01:43:24,546
Pretty women, yes

1465
01:43:24,613 --> 01:43:27,715
<i>Johanna, Johanna</i>

1466
01:43:27,783 --> 01:43:29,483
Pretty women

1467
01:43:29,552 --> 01:43:31,419
Pretty women are a wonder

1468
01:43:31,486 --> 01:43:33,120
Pretty women!

1469
01:43:33,188 --> 01:43:36,140
What we do for pretty women!

1470
01:43:36,208 --> 01:43:37,976
Blowing out their candles

1471
01:43:38,043 --> 01:43:39,910
Blowing out their candles

1472
01:43:39,979 --> 01:43:41,779
Or combing out their hair

1473
01:43:41,847 --> 01:43:43,514
Or combing out their hair

1474
01:43:43,582 --> 01:43:45,399
Then they leave

1475
01:43:45,467 --> 01:43:47,268
Even when they leave

1476
01:43:47,335 --> 01:43:49,070
Even when they
leave you and vanish

1477
01:43:49,138 --> 01:43:50,604
They still are there

1478
01:43:50,672 --> 01:43:52,073
They somehow can still remain

1479
01:43:52,141 --> 01:43:54,608
There with you, there

1480
01:43:54,676 --> 01:43:57,812
They're there

1481
01:43:57,880 --> 01:44:01,483
How seldom it is one
meets a fellow spirit.

1482
01:44:01,550 --> 01:44:06,137
With fellow tastes
in women, at least.

1483
01:44:06,588 --> 01:44:09,006
What's that?

1484
01:44:09,074 --> 01:44:11,959
The years, no doubt,
have changed me, sir.

1485
01:44:12,027 --> 01:44:14,996
But then, I suppose
the face of a barber,

1486
01:44:15,014 --> 01:44:19,217
the face of a prisoner, a dog,
is not particularly memorable.

1487
01:44:25,841 --> 01:44:28,542
Benjamin Barker.

1488
01:44:28,611 --> 01:44:31,479
Benjamin Barker!

1489
01:45:09,284 --> 01:45:12,870
Rest now, my friend

1490
01:45:14,923 --> 01:45:19,159
Rest now forever

1491
01:45:20,596 --> 01:45:25,916
Sleep now the untroubled

1492
01:45:25,984 --> 01:45:31,589
Sleep of the angels

1493
01:45:42,718 --> 01:45:44,986
Come for a shave, have you, lad?

1494
01:45:45,054 --> 01:45:46,654
No, I...

1495
01:45:50,408 --> 01:45:53,210
Everyone needs a good shave.

1496
01:46:00,452 --> 01:46:02,486
Forget my face.

1497
01:46:06,241 --> 01:46:09,560
Die! God in heaven, die!

1498
01:46:23,442 --> 01:46:24,859
You.

1499
01:46:33,802 --> 01:46:35,636
Why did you scream?

1500
01:46:35,704 --> 01:46:38,706
He was clutching onto me
dress, but he's finished now.

1501
01:46:38,773 --> 01:46:41,242
I'll take care of it.
Open the door.

1502
01:46:41,310 --> 01:46:43,644
Open the door, I said.

1503
01:47:37,749 --> 01:47:40,517
"Don't I know you?" she said.

1504
01:47:50,212 --> 01:47:52,079
You knew she lived.

1505
01:47:54,099 --> 01:47:56,317
I was only thinking of you.

1506
01:47:59,905 --> 01:48:01,889
You lied to me.

1507
01:48:01,957 --> 01:48:04,425
No, no, not lied at all

1508
01:48:04,493 --> 01:48:05,559
No, I never lied

1509
01:48:05,627 --> 01:48:07,328
Lucy...
Said she took a poison

1510
01:48:07,396 --> 01:48:09,346
She did, never said that she died

1511
01:48:09,415 --> 01:48:10,497
I've come home again

1512
01:48:10,565 --> 01:48:13,017
Poor thing, she lived
But it left her weak in the head

1513
01:48:13,085 --> 01:48:15,586
All she did for months
was just lie there in bed

1514
01:48:15,653 --> 01:48:17,038
Should've been in hospital

1515
01:48:17,106 --> 01:48:18,739
Wound up in Bedlam instead

1516
01:48:18,807 --> 01:48:19,957
Poor thing!

1517
01:48:20,025 --> 01:48:22,260
Better you should think she was dead
Oh, my God!

1518
01:48:22,294 --> 01:48:25,195
Yes, I lied 'cause I love you!

1519
01:48:25,264 --> 01:48:28,031
I'd be twice the wife she was!
Lucy...

1520
01:48:28,099 --> 01:48:29,267
I love you!

1521
01:48:29,334 --> 01:48:30,534
What have I done?

1522
01:48:30,602 --> 01:48:33,738
Could that thing have
cared for you like me?

1523
01:48:33,805 --> 01:48:35,839
Mrs. Lovett,
you're a bloody wonder

1524
01:48:35,907 --> 01:48:36,974
Eminently practical

1525
01:48:37,041 --> 01:48:38,542
And yet appropriate as always

1526
01:48:38,610 --> 01:48:39,977
As you've said repeatedly

1527
01:48:40,044 --> 01:48:41,545
There's little point
in dwelling on the past

1528
01:48:41,613 --> 01:48:42,680
Now, come here, my love...
Do you mean it?

1529
01:48:42,748 --> 01:48:44,047
Everything I did,
I swear, I thought

1530
01:48:44,115 --> 01:48:45,316
Was only for the best
Not a thing to fear

1531
01:48:45,384 --> 01:48:47,151
My love, what's dead ls dead

1532
01:48:47,218 --> 01:48:48,952
Can we still be married?

1533
01:48:49,020 --> 01:48:52,055
The history of the world, my pet

1534
01:48:52,123 --> 01:48:53,841
Oh, Mr. Todd, oh, Mr. Todd

1535
01:48:53,908 --> 01:48:55,376
Leave it to me

1536
01:48:55,444 --> 01:48:58,362
ls learn forgiveness
and try to forget

1537
01:48:58,430 --> 01:48:59,463
By the sea, Mr. Todd

1538
01:48:59,531 --> 01:49:00,531
We'll be comfy-cozy

1539
01:49:00,599 --> 01:49:01,632
By the sea, Mr. Todd

1540
01:49:01,699 --> 01:49:02,780
Where there's no one nosy

1541
01:49:02,834 --> 01:49:05,402
And life is for
the alive, my dear

1542
01:49:05,470 --> 01:49:07,538
So let's keep living it

1543
01:49:07,606 --> 01:49:12,175
Just keep living it,
really living it!

1544
01:49:58,873 --> 01:50:02,976
There was a barber and his wife

1545
01:50:04,329 --> 01:50:08,699
And she was beautiful

1546
01:50:11,302 --> 01:50:16,423
A foolish barber and his wife

1547
01:50:16,491 --> 01:50:20,928
She was his reason and his life

1548
01:50:21,697 --> 01:50:26,850
And she was beautiful

1549
01:50:26,868 --> 01:50:31,488
And she was virtuous

1550
01:50:33,691 --> 01:50:36,961
And he was...

